<a name="0">[0]</a> <a href="#0" id=0>They have a few indexing strategies, and a simple data manipulation language.</a>
<a name="1">[1]</a> <a href="#1" id=1>So, in our view they are simple database systems.</a>
<a name="2">[2]</a> <a href="#2" id=2>And, they have a collection of tools to create, access, search, and visualize the data.</a>
<a name="3">[3]</a> <a href="#3" id=3>They have a schema language (metadata) to define the metadata.</a>
<a name="4">[4]</a> <a href="#4" id=4>They have the start of non-procedural and parallel programming.</a>
<a name="5">[5]</a> <a href="#5" id=5>Database systems use files.</a>
<a name="6">[6]</a> <a href="#6" id=6>Lastly, most file systems can manage millions of files, but by the time a file system can deal with billions of files, it has become a database system.</a>
